{
    "publish_date": "2013-10-22T16:15:47.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT3M56S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "Water is the liquid of life.", 
            "dur": "2.062", 
            "start": "6.608"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We drink it,", 
            "dur": "0.722", 
            "start": "8.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we bathe in it,", 
            "dur": "0.853", 
            "start": "9.392"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we farm,", 
            "dur": "0.619", 
            "start": "10.245"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "cook,", 
            "dur": "0.332", 
            "start": "10.864"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and clean with it.", 
            "dur": "1.109", 
            "start": "11.196"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s the most abundant molecule in our bodies.", 
            "dur": "2.442", 
            "start": "12.305"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In fact, every life form we know of", 
            "dur": "1.784", 
            "start": "14.747"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "would die without it.", 
            "dur": "1.75", 
            "start": "16.531"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But most importantly, without water,", 
            "dur": "2.096", 
            "start": "18.281"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we wouldn&#39;t have", 
            "dur": "2.103", 
            "start": "20.377"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "iced tea.", 
            "dur": "0.946", 
            "start": "22.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Mmmm, iced tea.", 
            "dur": "2.647", 
            "start": "23.426"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Why do these ice cubes float?", 
            "dur": "2.122", 
            "start": "27.749"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If these were cubes of solid argon", 
            "dur": "2.049", 
            "start": "29.871"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in a cup of liquid argon,", 
            "dur": "1.904", 
            "start": "31.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they would sink.", 
            "dur": "1.161", 
            "start": "33.824"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And the same goes for most other substances.", 
            "dur": "2.652", 
            "start": "34.985"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But solid water, a.k.a. ice,", 
            "dur": "2.847", 
            "start": "37.637"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is somehow less dense than liquid water.", 
            "dur": "2.91", 
            "start": "40.484"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How&#39;s that possible?", 
            "dur": "1.828", 
            "start": "43.394"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You already know that every water molecule", 
            "dur": "1.705", 
            "start": "45.222"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is made up of two hydrogen atoms", 
            "dur": "2.043", 
            "start": "46.927"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "bonded to one oxygen atom.", 
            "dur": "2.344", 
            "start": "48.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let&#39;s look at a few of the molecules", 
            "dur": "1.368", 
            "start": "51.314"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in a drop of water,", 
            "dur": "1.491", 
            "start": "52.682"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and let&#39;s say the temperature is 25 degrees Celcius.", 
            "dur": "3.601", 
            "start": "54.173"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The molecules are bending,", 
            "dur": "1.597", 
            "start": "57.774"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "stretching,", 
            "dur": "0.704", 
            "start": "59.371"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "spinning,", 
            "dur": "0.624", 
            "start": "60.075"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and moving through space.", 
            "dur": "1.837", 
            "start": "60.699"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, let&#39;s lower the temperature,", 
            "dur": "2.206", 
            "start": "62.536"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which will reduce the amount of kinetic energy", 
            "dur": "1.872", 
            "start": "64.742"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "each of these molecules has", 
            "dur": "2.168", 
            "start": "66.614"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so they&#39;ll bend, stretch, spin, and move less.", 
            "dur": "2.883", 
            "start": "68.782"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that means that on average,", 
            "dur": "1.635", 
            "start": "71.665"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they&#39;ll take up less space.", 
            "dur": "2.161", 
            "start": "73.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, you&#39;d think that as the liquid water", 
            "dur": "1.631", 
            "start": "75.461"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "starts to freeze,", 
            "dur": "1.441", 
            "start": "77.092"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the molecules would just pack together", 
            "dur": "1.61", 
            "start": "78.533"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "more and more closely,", 
            "dur": "1.589", 
            "start": "80.143"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but that&#39;s not what happens.", 
            "dur": "2.011", 
            "start": "81.732"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Water has a special kind", 
            "dur": "1.344", 
            "start": "83.743"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of interaction between molecules", 
            "dur": "1.518", 
            "start": "85.087"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that most other substances don&#39;t have,", 
            "dur": "2.494", 
            "start": "86.605"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and it&#39;s called a hydrogen bond.", 
            "dur": "1.884", 
            "start": "89.099"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, remember that in a covalent bond", 
            "dur": "1.951", 
            "start": "90.983"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "two electrons are shared,", 
            "dur": "2.253", 
            "start": "92.934"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "usually unequally,", 
            "dur": "1.212", 
            "start": "95.187"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "between atoms.", 
            "dur": "1.21", 
            "start": "96.399"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In a hydrogen bond,", 
            "dur": "1.167", 
            "start": "97.609"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a hydrogen atom is shared, also unequally,", 
            "dur": "2.998", 
            "start": "98.776"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "between atoms.", 
            "dur": "1.616", 
            "start": "101.774"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One hydrogen bond looks like this.", 
            "dur": "2.734", 
            "start": "103.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Two look like this.", 
            "dur": "1.754", 
            "start": "106.124"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Here&#39;s three", 
            "dur": "0.906", 
            "start": "107.878"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and four", 
            "dur": "0.941", 
            "start": "108.784"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and five,", 
            "dur": "0.99", 
            "start": "109.725"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "six,", 
            "dur": "0.705", 
            "start": "110.715"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "seven,", 
            "dur": "0.544", 
            "start": "111.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "eight,", 
            "dur": "0.475", 
            "start": "111.964"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "nine,", 
            "dur": "0.481", 
            "start": "112.439"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "ten,", 
            "dur": "0.311", 
            "start": "112.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "eleven,", 
            "dur": "0.32", 
            "start": "113.231"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "twelve,", 
            "dur": "0.755", 
            "start": "113.551"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I could go on.", 
            "dur": "2.085", 
            "start": "114.306"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In a single drop of water,", 
            "dur": "1.385", 
            "start": "116.391"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "hydrogen bonds form extended networks", 
            "dur": "2.37", 
            "start": "117.776"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "between hundreds, thousands, millions,", 
            "dur": "1.888", 
            "start": "120.146"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "billions, trillions of molecules,", 
            "dur": "2.167", 
            "start": "122.034"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and these bonds are constantly breaking and reforming.", 
            "dur": "3.412", 
            "start": "124.201"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, back to our water as it cools down.", 
            "dur": "2.203", 
            "start": "127.613"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Above 4 degrees Celcius,", 
            "dur": "2.057", 
            "start": "129.816"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the kinetic energy of the water molecules", 
            "dur": "1.651", 
            "start": "131.873"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "keeps their interactions with each other short.", 
            "dur": "3.005", 
            "start": "133.524"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Hydrogen bonds form and break", 
            "dur": "1.921", 
            "start": "136.529"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "like high school relationships,", 
            "dur": "1.825", 
            "start": "138.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that is to say, quickly.", 
            "dur": "2.313", 
            "start": "140.275"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But below 4 degrees,", 
            "dur": "1.194", 
            "start": "142.588"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the kinetic energy of the water molecules", 
            "dur": "1.931", 
            "start": "143.782"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "starts to fall below the energy", 
            "dur": "2.063", 
            "start": "145.713"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of the hydrogen bonds.", 
            "dur": "1.895", 
            "start": "147.776"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, hydrogen bonds form much more frequently", 
            "dur": "2.631", 
            "start": "149.671"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "than they break", 
            "dur": "1.325", 
            "start": "152.302"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and beautiful structures start to emerge", 
            "dur": "1.852", 
            "start": "153.627"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "from the chaos.", 
            "dur": "1.634", 
            "start": "155.479"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is what solid water, ice,", 
            "dur": "2.339", 
            "start": "157.113"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "looks like on the molecular level.", 
            "dur": "2.494", 
            "start": "159.452"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Notice that the ordered, hexagonal structure", 
            "dur": "2.357", 
            "start": "161.946"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is less dense than the disordered structure", 
            "dur": "2.7", 
            "start": "164.303"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of liquid water.", 
            "dur": "1.736", 
            "start": "167.003"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And you know that if an object is less dense", 
            "dur": "2.202", 
            "start": "168.739"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "than the fluid it&#39;s in,", 
            "dur": "1.429", 
            "start": "170.941"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it will float.", 
            "dur": "1.276", 
            "start": "172.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, ice floats on water,", 
            "dur": "1.883", 
            "start": "173.646"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so what?", 
            "dur": "1.198", 
            "start": "175.529"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, let&#39;s consider a world without floating ice.", 
            "dur": "2.913", 
            "start": "176.727"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The coldest part of the ocean", 
            "dur": "1.359", 
            "start": "179.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "would be the pitch-black ocean floor,", 
            "dur": "2.238", 
            "start": "180.999"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "once frozen, always frozen.", 
            "dur": "1.925", 
            "start": "183.237"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Forget lobster rolls", 
            "dur": "1.407", 
            "start": "185.162"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "since crustaceans would lose their habitats,", 
            "dur": "1.923", 
            "start": "186.569"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or sushi since kelp forests wouldn&#39;t grow.", 
            "dur": "2.652", 
            "start": "188.492"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What would Canadian kids do in winter", 
            "dur": "2.117", 
            "start": "191.144"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "without pond hockey or ice fishing?", 
            "dur": "2.087", 
            "start": "193.261"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And forget James Cameron&#39;s Oscar", 
            "dur": "1.786", 
            "start": "195.348"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because the Titanic totally would have made it.", 
            "dur": "3.128", 
            "start": "197.134"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Say goodbye to the white polar ice caps", 
            "dur": "1.826", 
            "start": "200.262"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "reflecting sunlight", 
            "dur": "1.074", 
            "start": "202.088"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that would otherwise bake the planet.", 
            "dur": "1.937", 
            "start": "203.162"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In fact, forget the oceans as we know them,", 
            "dur": "2.193", 
            "start": "205.099"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which at over 70% of the Earth&#39;s surface area,", 
            "dur": "2.4", 
            "start": "207.292"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "regulate the atmosphere of the whole planet.", 
            "dur": "2.418", 
            "start": "209.692"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But worst of all,", 
            "dur": "1.338", 
            "start": "212.524"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "there would be no iced tea.", 
            "dur": "3.384", 
            "start": "213.862"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Mmmmm, iced tea.", 
            "dur": "3.138", 
            "start": "217.246"
        }
    ], 
